scope:
Daemon commit messages should use task metadata instead of opaque task IDs. Use the task title as the commit subject line, with task ID, class, deliverables, and the latest breadcrumb text in the body. For failures, append (attempt N) to the subject and include the failure type. Add git.commit_prefix to GitConfig (default 'wolfcastle') so users can customize or remove the prefix. Format: '{prefix}: {title}' as subject, then 'Task: {id} [{class}]
Deliverables: {files}

{latest breadcrumb}' as body. Implementation is in commitAfterIteration in internal/daemon/iteration.go. The daemon already reads node state before committing; pass the task title, class, deliverables, and latest breadcrumb into the commit message builder. The commit_prefix field goes in GitConfig with a default in Defaults().
